    "body": "<!-- devin-review-comment {\"id\": \"ANALYSIS_pr-review-job-7fb63ea0faef423bbf98674b4bd79ae8_0003\", \"file_path\": \"lib/validations.ts\", \"start_line\": 1, \"end_line\": 1, \"side\": \"RIGHT\"} -->\n\n🚩 **Zod v4 import pattern: `import { z } from 'zod'` is compatible but `@hookform/resolvers` compatibility should be verified**\n\nThe project uses `zod: ^4.3.6` and `@hookform/resolvers: ^5.2.2`. Zod v4 is a major version change from v3 with some API differences. The schemas in `lib/validations.ts` use basic Zod APIs (`z.object`, `z.string`, `z.enum`, `.default()`, `.optional()`, `.min()`, `.email()`, `.uuid()`) which are all present in Zod v4. However, the `@hookform/resolvers` package at v5.x was specifically built for Zod v4 compatibility via `@hookform/resolvers/zod`. I was not able to verify the installed versions from a lockfile (none exists), so the exact resolver used at runtime depends on npm resolution. This is worth confirming during CI/build.\n\n<!-- devin-review-badge-begin -->\n<a href=\"https://app.devin.ai/review/celaluysl/agencycrm/pull/3\" target=\"_blank\">\n  <picture>\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://static.devin.ai/assets/gh-open-in-devin-review-dark.svg?v=1\">\n    <img src=\"https://static.devin.ai/assets/gh-open-in-devin-review-light.svg?v=1\" alt=\"Open in Devin Review\">\n  </picture>\n</a>\n<!-- devin-review-badge-end -->\n\n---\n*Was this helpful? React with 👍 or 👎 to provide feedback.*",
