    "body": "<!-- devin-review-comment {\"id\": \"ANALYSIS_pr-review-job-0f3cf82bf82b4b4b8c83c409014bdc08_0006\", \"file_path\": \"lib/supabase/client.ts\", \"start_line\": 4, \"end_line\": 8, \"side\": \"RIGHT\"} -->\n\n🚩 **Supabase browser client is created per-call without singleton pattern**\n\nAt `lib/supabase/client.ts:4-8`, `createClient()` creates a new Supabase browser client on every invocation. The Supabase docs recommend creating a singleton for browser clients to avoid redundant auth state management and WebSocket connections. If multiple components call `createClient()` independently, each gets a separate client instance with its own auth listener and realtime subscription handling. The `@supabase/ssr` `createBrowserClient` may handle deduplication internally (it uses a global store), but this should be verified to avoid unnecessary resource overhead.\n\n<!-- devin-review-badge-begin -->\n<a href=\"https://app.devin.ai/review/celaluysl/agencycrm/pull/3\" target=\"_blank\">\n  <picture>\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://static.devin.ai/assets/gh-open-in-devin-review-dark.svg?v=1\">\n    <img src=\"https://static.devin.ai/assets/gh-open-in-devin-review-light.svg?v=1\" alt=\"Open in Devin Review\">\n  </picture>\n</a>\n<!-- devin-review-badge-end -->\n\n---\n*Was this helpful? React with 👍 or 👎 to provide feedback.*",
